          "text": [
            "<p><strong>3.  </strong>Describe three real life situations in which opposite quantities combine to make 0.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "NOVeXy2ZM0ogXrpd",
        "title": "Text 17",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Answers will vary. Possible answers: The temperature rises 20ºF during the day, then decreases 20ºF at night so the overall temperature change is 0ºF. You walk ½ a mile to school in the morning and then walk ½ a mile to go home in the afternoon, so your overall change in position is zero. You spent $10 on supplies to make bracelets and then earn $10 by selling them, so your overall profit is $0. I ride up 3 floors on an elevator, then I ride down 3 floors. I end up on the same floor that I started.</p>"
          ]
        }
