          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Situation D. The Game of Zero</strong></p><p>After analyzing and representing moves on the chip board, Amber creates the Game of Zero.</p><p>Play the Game of Zero. Describe some winning strategies. </p><p>Equipment</p><ul><li>black and red chips </li><li>chipboard</li><li>number cube</li><li>chipboard cards</li></ul><p>Rules (play as teams or individuals)</p><ul><li>A chipboard card is chosen randomly</li><li>All teams set-up a chipboard to match the chipboard card</li><li>Each team takes turns rolling a number cube. The team decides to add (red or black) or subtract (red or black) that number of chips from the board.</li><li>The team that gets their board down to zero first wins. </li></ul>"
          ]
